libhammer (3.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add a standalone migration tool for updating Hammer 2.x C and C++ sources
    to the Hammer 3 public data structures
  * Support preview, check, and in-place migration modes
  * Preserve source formatting and avoid rewriting comments, literals, and
    unrelated member accesses

 -- Mahmoud Elbasiouny <melbasiouny@riversideresearch.org>  Wed, 22 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0400

libhammer (3.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Restore context-free and regular-expression parsing backends
  * Add capped repetition parsers h_many_cap and h_many1_cap
  * Add discriminator-based dispatch parsing and backend support
  * Add sequence removal APIs and allocator reallocation support
  * Extend h_bytes and related combinators across supported backends
  * Add h_float16, h_float32, and h_float64 IEEE 754 parsers
  * Improve parser parameter validation, runtime checks, and error handling
  * Name public token and timestamp unions and widen token bit lengths to size_t
  * Remove h_arena_free in favor of arena-owned allocation lifetimes
  * Enforce strict C99 compliance

 -- Mahmoud Elbasiouny <melbasiouny@riversideresearch.org>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0400

libhammer (2.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rename MicroHammer packaging and documentation back to Hammer
  * Update Debian source and binary package names from libmicrohammer to libhammer
  * Remove obsolete pkg-config variant metadata now that only one Hammer variant ships
  * Add Go language bindings, tests, and documentation
  * Add DNS, NTP, and TFTP protocol parser examples
  * Add DNS valid and malformed packet fixtures and TFTP parser tests
  * Move legacy examples under examples/old
  * Update example builds to prefer the checkout-local Hammer build and fall back to pkg-config libhammer
  * Add gcc to build dependencies and documented prerequisites
  * Clean generated Java binding outputs before regeneration to prevent stale SWIG wrappers from breaking binding builds
  * Fix Python binding version detection to read the top-level VERSION file
  * Bump project and Python binding package versions to 2.1.0

 -- Mahmoud Elbasiouny <melbasiouny@riversideresearch.org>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0400

libmicrohammer (2.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Widen HToken.len and bits_env.length from uint8_t to size_t, fixing silent
    integer truncation for tokens and bit counts exceeding 255 (closes #3)
  * Introduce HAMMER_ASSERT in internal.h: unconditional abort for programmer
    errors that survives -DNDEBUG; replaces assert()-based guards in bitwriter.c,
    glue.c, glue.h, and datastructures.c (closes #6)
  * Update h_assert_type macro to abort on type mismatch via HAMMER_ASSERT
  * Update token length test to verify 256-byte tokens parse correctly
  * Add ruff linting of Python and SCons files to CI pipeline

 -- Mahmoud Elbasiouny <melbasiouny@riversideresearch.org>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 12:00:00 -0400

libmicrohammer (2.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Reintroduce Python, Java/JNI, and C++ language bindings
  * Add SWIG-based Python bindings with unittest smoke tests
  * Add SWIG-based Java/JNI bindings with standalone smoke tests and hammer.jar packaging
